  "prompt": "What are the main parts of the digestive system? How do they function?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of the main parts of the digestive system and their functions:\n\n1. Mouth\n- Begins digestion through chewing (mechanical breakdown)\n- Produces saliva containing enzymes to start chemical digestion\n- Breaks down food into smaller pieces\n\n2. Esophagus\n- Muscular tube that connects mouth to stomach\n- Moves food through peristalsis (wave-like muscle contractions)\n- Prevents food from returning to mouth\n\n3. Stomach\n- Stores and breaks down food\n- Produces stomach acid and digestive enzymes\n- Churns food into a liquid mixture called chyme\n- Begins protein digestion\n\n4. Small Intestine\n- Primary site of nutrient absorption\n- Continues chemical digestion with help from pancreatic enzymes\n- Breaks down carbohydrates, proteins, and fats\n- Absorbs nutrients into bloodstream through tiny finger-like projections (villi)\n\n5. Large Intestine (Colon)\n- Absorbs water and remaining nutrients\n- Forms and stores waste (feces)\n- Houses beneficial bacteria\n- Completes digestion process\n\n6. Liver\n- Produces bile to help digest fats\n- Processes nutrients\n- Detoxifies harmful substances\n\n7. Pancreas\n- Produces digestive enzymes\n- Releases insulin to regulate blood sugar\n\nThese organs work together to break down food, extract nutrients, and eliminate waste.",
